      "Platform reboarded April 24, 2025",
      "Secondary containment measures installed (acyclic berm)"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 21, 2025, at approximately 19:30hrs CDT, the West Delta 90 B platform experienced a loss of well control during Plug and Abandonment operations on well B020. While pumping fluid down the tubing to equalize pressure across a downhole plug, approximately 20 barrels of oil and gas were released from a leak at the starter head flange and 10-3/4 x 20 surface casing annulus. The uncontrolled release led to full platform evacuation. The incident resulted from a breach at the spooling head and failure within the tubing string that enabled hydraulic communication between tubing and annulus. Contributing factors included inadequate pre-job planning, failure to incorporate historical well data showing prior leakage issues, and lack of hazard assessment before continuing operations after initial leak detection.",
    "recommendations": [
      "The BSEE New Orleans District has no recommendations at this time"
    ],
